  "description": "Recombination is the epoch approximately 380,000 years after the [Big Bang](./big-bang.md) when the universe cooled to about 3,000 kelvin -- cool enough for free electrons to combine with atomic nuclei to form neutral atoms. This made the universe transparent to [light](../../../terms/light.md) for the first time.",
